{
  "stem": "7160.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When the people start dying, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] they make a thing-- a [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It means if people were to die, they have to bury them somewhere.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they picked me up with a few other people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had two big trucks, two big wagons with wheels.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we used to put them around the shoulder, and we used to carry them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in each one, we used to put about 100 dead people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "From all 11 camps that had died, I used to bury them, with the other people, not all by myself.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we used to put 200, 300 like sardines-- head, foot, foot, head, like that, you know?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Like the head here, the foot here, then turn around, you know, pile all that up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We used to dig a hole maybe about 10 feet deep, and maybe almost as big as this room here.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we used to put about 200 people dead there, pile up one on top of the other one.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So then after we work there for, I would say, about 8, 9 months.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Right around 1945-- it was February, I think it was, because I remember the snow-- so all of a sudden, they took us from there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They said they closed the camp, and they was going to take us somewhere.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They don't say where.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we just keep marching, day in and day out, day in and day out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we  didn't know where we were going.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then finally, we hear they're going to take us in a deserted place, and they're going to shoot every one of us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A friend if mine, he spoke-- his name was Daniel Hazan.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I got a picture from him.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
